claim.claim-text:
1. A method of forming a semiconductor device from a semiconductor wafer, the wafer having a front and a back, the method comprising the following steps: 
a) forming a layer of material over the front and back of the wafer; 
b) forming a layer of resist over the front of the wafer and leaving at least a portion of said layer of material over the front of the wafer exposed; 
c) removing said layer of material from the back of the wafer; 
d) simultaneously with step c), removing at least a portion of said exposed portion of said layer of material over the front of the wafer.

3. The method of claim 1 wherein said layer of material is a first layer of material and said layer of resist is a first layer of resist, further comprising the following steps: 
e) forming a second layer of material over the front and back of the wafer and over said first layer of material between steps a) and b); 
f) forming a second layer of resist subsequent to step d) leaving at least a portion of said first layer of material exposed; 
g) etching said exposed portion of said first layer to expose the semiconductor wafer.

8. A method of forming a semiconductor device from a semiconductor wafer, the wafer having a front and a back, the method comprising the following steps: 
a) forming a nitride layer over the front and back of the wafer; 
b) forming a layer of resist over the front of the wafer and leaving at least a portion of said nitride layer over the front of the wafer exposed; 
c) removing said nitride layer from the back of the wafer; 
d) simultaneously with step c), removing at least a portion of said exposed portion of said nitride layer over the front of the wafer.

10. The method of claim 8 wherein said nitride layer is a first nitride layer and said layer of resist is a first layer of resist, further comprising the following steps: 
e) forming a second nitride layer over the front and back of the wafer and over said first nitride layer between steps a) and b); 
f) forming a second layer of resist subsequent to step d) leaving at least a portion of said first nitride layer exposed; 
g) etching said exposed portion of said first nitride layer to expose the semiconductor wafer.

14. A method of forming a transistor for a semiconductor device from a semiconductor wafer, the wafer having a front and a back, the method comprising the following steps: 
a) forming a nitride layer over the front and back of the wafer; 
b) forming a spacer layer over the front and back of the wafer and over said nitride layer; 
c) forming a first resist layer over the front of the wafer and leaving at least a portion of said spacer layer over the front of the wafer exposed; 
d) removing said nitride layer and said spacer layer from the back of the wafer; 
e) simultaneously with step d), removing at least a portion of said exposed portion of said spacer layer over the front of the wafer; 
f) removing said first resist layer; 
g) spacer etching said spacer layer to form spacers; 
h) forming a second layer of resist subsequent to step e) leaving at least a portion of said nitride layer exposed; 
i) etching said exposed portion of said nitride layer and to expose the semiconductor wafer.

15. A method of forming a transistor for a semiconductor device from a semiconductor wafer, the wafer having a front and a back, the method comprising the following steps: 
a) forming a nitride layer over the front and back of the wafer; 
b) forming a first resist layer over the front of the wafer and leaving at least a portion of said nitride layer over the front of the wafer exposed; 
c) removing said nitride layer from the back of the wafer; 
d) simultaneously with step c), removing at least a portion of said exposed portion of said nitride layer over the front of the wafer; 
e) forming a second layer of resist subsequent to step d) leaving at any remaining exposed portion of said nitride layer exposed; 
f) etching any remaining portion of said exposed portion of said nitride layer and exposing the semiconductor wafer.
